The paper deals with the segmentation of knee cartilage using MRI images, which is a common problem in medical imaging. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of diffusion tensor imaging (DTI) to assess compositional changes in the cartilage extracellular matrix, which is a specific technique used in medical imaging. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category.
